		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Perspective is off.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.drawinghowtodraw.com/drawing-lessons/Perspective-Drawing/2-Two-Point-Perspective.html">http://www.drawinghowtodraw.com/drawing ... ctive.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />The only thing that is really proper perspective is that 'show girls' sign, and maybe the building in the back.<br /><br />Also, size of buildings. If a window is reasonably up to 10 feet wide, then that building to the left of the 'show girls' sign looks like its about 30 feet by 30 feet, tops. Actual buildings are usually over 100 feet, maybe even 300+ feet long.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
