		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think it's good you leave uneven space for the second layer to show through. The yellow-light brown building is the one that stands out as aesthetically different, if that is enough confirmation on what you already wrote in the OP. The scene reminds me of the mixed architecture at current time alexanderplatz, though seen through a sci fi cartoon shimmer.<br /><br /><br />I tthought the warped perspective was intended? Whether or not, if anyone's interested, Martin Jay's article on <a href="http://beauty.gmu.edu/AVT307/AVT307-001/martin%20jay%20vision%20and%20visuality%20copy.pdf" class="postlink">scopic regimes</a> is relevant and a good short read for any artist working with scenes or generally interested in the craft of projecting a state of perception unto the viewer.

		

